    <h2>HTML Basics</h2>
    <p>HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the standard language for creating web pages. It uses tags to structure content.</p>
    <h3>Common HTML Tags</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><code>&lt;h1&gt; to &lt;h6&gt;</code>: Headings</li>
        <li><code>&lt;p&gt;</code>: Paragraphs</li>
        <li><code>&lt;a&gt;</code>: Links</li>
        <li><code>&lt;ul&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;ol&gt;</code>: Unordered and ordered lists</li>
        <li><code>&lt;li&gt;</code>: List items</li>
        <li><code>&lt;img&gt;</code>: Images</li>
        <li><code>&lt;div&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;span&gt;</code>: Containers for styling</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Image example</h3>
    <p>Outside image link below - we link to outside image. In general we want to link to images we control. It is considered not a great practice to hotlink to images you do not control</p>
    <img src="https://www.rtu.lv/images/logo_lv.svg?v=1.1" alt="RTU university">
    <h3>MDN reference for tags</h3>
    <p>For a comprehensive list of HTML tags and their usage, visit the <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element">MDN Web Docs HTML element reference</a>.</p>
